    <item>
      <title>Evergreen notes</title>
      <link>http://cashpw.com/posts/eb88f117-4925-42c7-a9cf-5789987fd933/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 Feb 2022 07:24:00 -0800</pubDate>
      <guid>http://cashpw.com/posts/eb88f117-4925-42c7-a9cf-5789987fd933/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://cashpw.com/posts/df479fb9-f7b0-4e3a-a7eb-41849fbc190e/&#34;&gt;Andy Matuschak&lt;/a&gt;&amp;rsquo;s idea of an evergreen note is one which is &amp;ldquo;written and organized to evolve, contribute, and accumulate over time, across projects&amp;rdquo;. I see it as the Unix philosophy applied to writing and note taking.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;bibliography&#34;&gt;&#xA;Bibliography&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#bibliography&#34; class=&#34;heading-anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;style&gt;.csl-entry{text-indent: -1.5em; margin-left: 1.5em;}&lt;/style&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;csl-bib-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;backlinks&#34;&gt;&#xA;Backlinks&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#backlinks&#34; class=&#34;heading-anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://cashpw.com/posts/df479fb9-f7b0-4e3a-a7eb-41849fbc190e/&#34;&gt;Andy Matuschak&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://cashpw.com/posts/2c8acd36-620a-47a7-8d3a-63594fd2065c/&#34;&gt;Andy Matuschak | Write Notes for Yourself by Default, Disregarding Audience&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Personal knowledge management</title>
      <link>http://cashpw.com/posts/773406e0-fe95-41f4-a254-b2c6ade18ce9/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 Feb 2022 07:20:00 -0800</pubDate>
      <guid>http://cashpw.com/posts/773406e0-fe95-41f4-a254-b2c6ade18ce9/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Personal knowledge management (PKM) is a process of collecting information that a person uses to gather, classify, store, search, retrieve and share knowledge in their daily activities and the way in which these processes support work activities. It is a response to the idea that knowledge workers need to be responsible for their own growth and learning.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href=&#34;#citeproc_bib_item_1&#34;&gt;“Personal Knowledge Management” 2022&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;bibliography&#34;&gt;&#xA;Bibliography&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#bibliography&#34; class=&#34;heading-anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;style&gt;.csl-entry{text-indent: -1.5em; margin-left: 1.5em;}&lt;/style&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;csl-bib-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;csl-entry&#34;&gt;&lt;a id=&#34;citeproc_bib_item_1&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;“Personal Knowledge Management.” 2022. In &lt;i&gt;Wikipedia&lt;/i&gt;. &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Personal_knowledge_management&amp;oldid=1112158308&#34;&gt;https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Personal_knowledge_management&amp;#38;oldid=1112158308&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;backlinks&#34;&gt;&#xA;Backlinks&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#backlinks&#34; class=&#34;heading-anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://cashpw.com/posts/fc2ae791-d310-46b9-9e30-19ca765cac1d/&#34;&gt;Notes should be private by default&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://cashpw.com/posts/b130e6f2-31a1-4c3a-ae8b-7d8208a69710/&#34;&gt;Zettelkasten&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
    </item>
